// Setup command skeleton — guided first-run onboarding.
//
// Modeled on basecamp-cli's setup/wizard command. Detects first-run
// condition (no credentials + no token env + interactive TTY) and
// walks the user through authentication and initial configuration.
//
// Recommended flow:
//   1. Welcome           — brief intro, what setup will do
//   2. Authentication    — run auth login (OAuth, PAT, etc.)
//   3. Account Selection — if multiple accounts, pick one
//   4. Project Selection — optional: pick a default project/workspace
//   5. Save Config       — write to global or local config, ask user
//   6. Summary           — show what was configured, next steps
